isoiec80000:term-t7-35.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "linear absorption coefficient <radiometry>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "alpha_\"l\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "a_\"l\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "alpha"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-35.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-35.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-35.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-2 ;
  skos:definition """relative decrease in radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) caused by absorption"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case, \"spectral\" is added before this quantity name.

The spectral linear absorption coefficient can be expressed by the relative decrease in the spectral radiant flux, stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)], with respect to propagation length, stem:[l], of a collimated beam at a point in an absorbing medium

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha_\"l\"(lambda) = 1/(Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)) (\"d\"Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda))/(\"d\"l)
++++

It can also be expressed as a function of transmittance (<<t7-31.5>>).

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha_\"l\" = -\"ln\"(tau)//l = A_\"n\"//l
++++

The linear absorption coefficient is that part of the linear attenuation coefficient (<<t7-35.1>>) that is due to absorption. Scattering might also contribute.

Similarly, luminous and photon quantities can be defined.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .